Info.Name: Pine
Info.Desc: A pine that grows in a colder region. Its fruits make precious spices.

Info.Name: Great Pine
Info.Desc: A pine tree that has been growing at the foothill for long. It's deeply rooted on a cliff.

Info.Name: Palm Tree
Info.Desc: A tree that can tolerate sandy soil and sea breeze, and likes resorts. Its fruits can be used in cooking and alchemy.

Info.Name: Great Palm Tree
Info.Desc: A great palm tree growing up freely and naturally. Arcticus likes to eat its fruit.

Info.Name: Oak Tree
Info.Desc: A useful tree both for humans and animals, which produces Antidote Berries.

Info.Name: Test Oak Tree
Info.Desc: A tree even children can log with ease. Swords don't work on it, but axes can fell it easily. How strange!

Info.Name: Blue Oak Tree
Info.Desc: An oak tree that has been affected by the aura of the forest and turned green. It grants slightly more XP.

Info.Name: Great Oak Tree
Info.Desc: An old oak tree that may provide Elder Logs. Oak fruit will drop if you log it.

Info.Name: Hidden Great Tree
Info.Desc: An oak tree discovered by Mayna, growing in a hidden place. It's her first notable spoil as a Woodcutter.

Info.Name: Great Blue Oak Tree
Info.Desc: A green oak that, affected by forest power, has become huge. It grants slightly more XP than the Great Oak Tree.

Info.Name: Skytree
Info.Desc: A hard but flexible living tree. It provides Rejuvenating Berries.

Info.Name: Great Skytree
Info.Desc: A great tree growing silently on Levitania. It sometimes drops rare Elder Logs.

Info.Name: Mangrove
Info.Desc: A tree that likes the sea. It can even thrive in shallow waters. You can hear the ocean in its trunk.

Info.Name: Great Mangrove
Info.Desc: An old mangrove growing in sea water. Its roots are home to many fishes.

Info.Name: Sugar Tree
Info.Desc: A draught-tolerant tree often seen in Al Maajik. The sweet fruit it produces can be used in place of sugar.

Info.Name: Great Sugar Tree
Info.Desc: A huge sugar tree growing up in blinding sandstorms. Travelers can rest in its shade during the scorching daytime.

Info.Name: White Fir
Info.Desc: A pine covered in snow, growing on the summit.

Info.Name: Great White Fir
Info.Desc: A fir that has been growing in a remote mountain, in order to escape humans looking for elder logs and great trees.

Info.Name: Starry Tree
Info.Desc: A tree growing up on an isolated island listening to the conversations of the stars. It provides Rejuvenating Berries just like firs.

Info.Name: Great Starry Tree
Info.Desc: A Starry Tree that has been listening to the conversations of the stars. It finally managed to join the conversations.

Info.Name: Great Elderwood Tree
Info.Desc: A great tree that has been alive since birth. Only Woodcutters whom it acknowledges can log it.

Info.Name: Great Elderwood Tree
Info.Desc: A great tree that has been alive since birth. Only Woodcutters whom it acknowledges can log it.

Info.Name: Sinister Tree
Info.Desc: A great tree that has been taking in the evil aura lingering in the forest. Its arms are hard yet flexible.

Info.Name: Celestial Tree
Info.Desc: A great tree covered in soft white leaves. Its leaves resemble a piece of cloud when viewed from below.

Info.Name: Sacred Fire Tree
Info.Desc: A divine tree watered by lava. Also known as the Fire Elemental Tree.

Info.Name: Sacred Wind Tree
Info.Desc: A desert divine tree with wind blowing in its trunk. Also known as the Wind Elemental Tree.

Info.Name: Sacred Water Tree
Info.Desc: A divine tree watered by the ocean current that has travelled all the seas. Also known as the Water Elemental Tree.

Info.Name: Sacred Earth Tree
Info.Desc: A divine tree growing in the rich soil of the plains. Also known as the Earth Elemental Tree.

Info.Name: Sacred Earth Tree
Info.Desc: A divine tree growing in the rich soil of the plains. Also known as the Earth Elemental Tree.

Info.Name: Dessert Tree
Info.Desc: A tree heading for the Subterranean Lake in search of water. It provides Antipara Berries.

Info.Name: Great Dessert Tree
Info.Desc: A Desert Tree that has spent years by the Subterranean Lake. Views sharks and humans who log giant trees as its enemies.

Info.Name: Copper Deposit
Info.Desc: A common deposit you can find anywhere. With a low melting point and easy to process, it can be used in many ways.

Info.Name: Test Copper Deposit
Info.Desc: A deposit for beginners. Don't tell anyone that the master has left a crack in it.

Info.Name: Gold Deposit
Info.Desc: A great deposit from which you can mine precious gold. Some may contain sandstones only, though.

Info.Name: Platinum Deposit
Info.Desc: A romantic deposit on the snowfield, which emits whitish light.

Info.Name: Magic Deposit
Info.Desc: A mysterious deposit emitting an evil light. It may contain mana-free sandstones.

Info.Name: Magma Deposit
Info.Desc: A deposit full of the essence of magma. Approach it and you'll feel the earth.

Info.Name: Silver Deposit
Info.Desc: A deposit that arouses melancholy in the moonlight. It contains precious Port Puerto Silver.

Info.Name: Marine Deposit
Info.Desc: The result of agelong crystalizing of deep-sea minerals. You can mine Marine Ore if you're lucky, and Minty Ore if you're not.

Info.Name: Iron Deposit
Info.Desc: The source of iron, the most important industrial material. It's especially important when making armor.

Info.Name: Rainbow Deposit
Info.Desc: A rare deposit that contains the legendary Celestial Ore. You may end up with nothing but Minty Ore, though.

Info.Name: Great Copper Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge copper deposit typically found in Castele. You may end up getting Minty Ore from it, though.

Info.Name: Great Gold Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge gold deposit that has been growing secretly underground. You can obtain Mana Holy Stone from its Chest.

Info.Name: Great Platinum Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge platinum deposit. It reflects sunlight like a piece of ice that will never melt.

Info.Name: Great Magic Deposit
Info.Desc: A crystal of darkness said to be blacker than the heart of a Dark Sultan. The Black Onyx lies at the darkest part of it.

Info.Name: Great Magma Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge magma deposit. The heat it emits reflects the vitality of the earth.

Info.Name: Great Silver Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge silver deposit affected by sea water. You can obtain Battle Holy Stone from its Chest.

Info.Name: Great Marine Deposit
Info.Desc: A marine deposit that may contain gemstones. You can obtain Guardian Divine Rock from its Chest.

Info.Name: Great Iron Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge iron deposit growing up in the depth of cave. You can obtain Gear Enh. Orb from its Chest.

Info.Name: Great Rainbow Deposit
Info.Desc: A rainbow deposit that has absorbed many rainbows. You can obtain Sky Rock from its Chest.

Info.Name: Yellow Crystal
Info.Desc: A Yellow Crystal that has absorbed much clean mountain air and water. You can mine Yellow Stones and Minty Ores from it.

Info.Name: Great Yellow Crystal
Info.Desc: A huge Yellow Crystal occasionally found in Mt Snowpeak Foothill. It's very hard, and you may mine Topaz from it.

Info.Name: Great Crystal
Info.Desc: A crystal that quietly formed without anyone knowing. Aim at the Sweet Spot and you can mine it with ease.

Info.Name: Blue Crystal
Info.Desc: A blue crystal that has absorbed water dripping from the cave roof. You can mine Blue Stones and Minty Ores from it.

Info.Name: Red Crystal
Info.Desc: A red crystal discovered near lava. Miners can hardly resist that fire-like color.

Info.Name: White Crystal
Info.Desc: A crystal as white like snow and as transparent as ice.

Info.Name: Superior Marine Deposit
Info.Desc: A crystal of condensed sea water, containing Amethyst. It's usually not mature yet, and you can mine Purple Stones from it.

Info.Name: Superior Magic Deposit
Info.Desc: A black crystal emitting a dark aura. You can mine Black Onyx from it if you are lucky enough.

Info.Name: Superior Rainbow Deposit
Info.Desc: A crystal of rainbow light, which shines like a diamond. It may sometimes only contain Minty Ores, though.

Info.Name: Great Blue Crystal
Info.Desc: A huge blue crystal occasionally found in Waterfall Cave. You can obtain Aquamarines from its Chest.

Info.Name: Great Red Crystal
Info.Desc: A huge red crystal. Emitting red light in a cave, it's said to be the lantern of the earth.

Info.Name: Great White Crystal
Info.Desc: A huge white crystal. It's like a claymore towering in the snowfield, arousing awe in those who see it.

Info.Name: Amazing Marine Deposit
Info.Desc: A superior marine deposit growing under high water pressure. You can obtain Ocean Dew from the its Chest.

Info.Name: Amazing Gold Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge superior gold deposit occasionally found in Skeleton Cave. You can obtain Oasis Stone from its Chest.

Info.Name: Amazing Magic Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge darkness crystal born from the darkness in the ruins. You can obtain Age-Old Rock from its Chest.

Info.Name: Amazing Rainbow Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge rainbow crystal that has absorbed much heavenly light. You can obtain Heavenly Light from its Chest.

Info.Name: Enormous Ancient Fossil
Info.Desc: A gigantic fossil that can move archaeology maniacs to tears. You can obtain Gigantic Fossil from its Chest.

Info.Name: Dragon Scab
Info.Desc: A deposit whose hardness and shape resembles a dragon. You can obtain a Chest of the same name from it.

Info.Name: Dark Heart
Info.Desc: A deposit whose hardness and shape resembles a dragon. You can obtain a Chest of the same name from it.

Info.Name: Fire Wingrock
Info.Desc: A fire crystal that emits light both day and night. Also known as the Fire Rock.

Info.Name: Wind Wingrock
Info.Desc: A wind crystal surrounded by small hurricanes. Also known as the Wind Rock.

Info.Name: Water Wingrock
Info.Desc: A water crystal that boosts humidity of it surroundings. Also known as the Water Rock.

Info.Name: Earth Wingrock
Info.Desc: An earth crystal that absorbs energy from the depth of earth. Also known as the Earth Rock.

Info.Name: Ancient Fossil
Info.Desc: A fossil that reveals the mysteries from ancient times. It's the remnant of the ancestors of Napdragons, which have long been extinct.

Info.Name: Golem Stone
Info.Desc: A golem stone born from ores brought back by the Crowned Champion from Lava Cave. It will become a golem when it obtains life.

Info.Name: Blackiron Deposit
Info.Desc: A deposit that forms from the winds of the prairie and the sea. Its color is a bluish black, the complexity of which is charming.

Info.Name: Great Blackiron Deposit
Info.Desc: A huge blackiron deposit consisted of ores from both land and sea. It occasionally contains Blackiron Ore.

Info.Name: Haniwa Deposit
Info.Desc: A rare deposit particular to Haniwa Cave. Ancient civilizations used to carve statues of the Haniwa Clansman into the ores.

Info.Name: Great Haniwa Deposit
Info.Desc: A great Haniwa deposit particular to Haniwa Cave. Haniwa Stones are popular souvenirs.

Info.Name: Westwood
Info.Desc: An oak tree that grows by the seaside, bathing in sea breeze. Being green, inside and out, it's named a green oak.

Info.Name: Great Westwood
Info.Desc: A green oak that has survived harsh environments. Its fruit is a popular spice.

Info.Name: Green Crystal
Info.Desc: A green crystal born from gales that sweep the earth. You can obtain Novel Green Ore and Quality Minty Ore from it.

Info.Name: Great Green Crystal
Info.Desc: A great green crystal occasionally found in the west plains. You can obtain Emerald from its Chest.

Info.Name: Huge Copper Deposit
Info.Desc: A giant copper deposit. It is carefully hidden by the Molays.

Info.Name: Moon Crystal
Info.Desc: A crescent-shaped ore only found in Mt Snowpeak. It emits yellowish light just like the actual crescent moon.

Info.Name: Holy Blackiron Stone
Info.Desc: A huge sword-shaped deposit that resists Miners. It is protected by the spirits of mined deposits.

Info.Name: Century-Old Oak
Info.Desc: A 100-year-old oak tree that is very thick. It emits a faint smell of honey.

Info.Name: Millennium Pine
Info.Desc: A 1000-year-old shiny pine. It has grown up in a place surrounded by waters and close to the moon.

Info.Name: Eternal Oak
Info.Desc: An oak tree that silently watches what's happening in the forest. Affected by spirits, it houses mana in its trunk.

Info.Name: Superior Oak
Info.Desc: A superior oak surrounded by trees. It bears blue berries due to change in its living environment.

Info.Name: Superior Great Oak
Info.Desc: A superior oak that has spent countless years in the forest as if sleeping. The green leaves with multiple layers are very popular.

Info.Name: Star Crystal
Info.Desc: A star-shaped crystal that looks like a meteorite. It is bluish and transparent, like the waterdrops in caves.

Info.Name: Palm of Titan
Info.Desc: An extremely hard ore known as the "Pickaxe Destroyer." They say it somehow resembles a fist.

Info.Name: Great Earth Deposit
Info.Desc: Great Earth Deposit (description) Backup Slot of Resources

Info.Name: Great Fire Deposit
Info.Desc: Great Fire Deposit (description) Backup Slot of Resources

Info.Name: Great Water Deposit
Info.Desc: Great Water Deposit (description) Backup Slot of Resources

Info.Name: Great Wind Deposit
Info.Desc: Great Wind Deposit (description) Backup Slot of Resources

Info.Name: Earth Deposit
Info.Desc: Earth Deposit (description) Backup Slot of Resources

Info.Name: Fire Deposit
Info.Desc: Fire Deposit (description) Backup Slot of Resources

Info.Name: Earthquake Bass
Info.Desc: A giant earth fish born from a crack in the ground.

Info.Name: Flame Bass
Info.Desc: A red-hot giant fish appearing in the lava.

Info.Name: Anemo Bass
Info.Desc: A giant fish of wind that travels from one water to another.

Info.Name: Torrent Bass
Info.Desc: A fastest giant fish which generates whirlpool when swimming.

Info.Name: Wobble Fish
Info.Desc: A powerful giant fish that can turn a boat over.

Info.Name: Hot Fish
Info.Desc: A troublesome big fish that increases the water temperature around it.

Info.Name: Sunder Fish
Info.Desc: A big fish too dangerous to touch. It can cut seaweeds and fishing lines into pieces.

Info.Name: Vortex Fish
Info.Desc: A big fish that swims in circles in a fixed place, generating water currents.

Info.Name: Divine Oak
Info.Desc: A legendary great tree known as the "Guardian of the Forest" and the "Intelligent Divine Tree". They say it will entrust its new shoots to Woodcutters it acknowledges.

Info.Name: Great Earth Stone
Info.Desc: A mysterious ore said to be intelligent. It emits brighter light when facing a Miner it acknowledges.

Info.Name: Leg. Grand Wingstone
Info.Desc: An ore that resembles huge wings. They say only Miners acknowledged as Heroes by the ore itself can mine it.

Info.Name: Scorching Dragon Stone
Info.Desc: A special ore that resembles a dragon. It throws fire from the cracks. Only well-prepared Miners can get to it.

Info.Name: Grizzly Oak Tree
Info.Desc: A giant tree whose leaves resemble the face of bears. They say you need to be as strong as a bear to log this tree, so it's seen as a symbol of strength.

Info.Name: Staff of Giant
Info.Desc: A giant tree said to be used by giants to make staffs. Tall as it is, seldom can any Woodcutter find it. The reason remains unknown.

Info.Name: Rainbow Flying Fish
Info.Desc: A dreamy fish said to be able to fly. It has grown too big to leave the water, though.

Info.Name: Serpent Tree
Info.Desc: A tree which resembles two snakes intertwined. Sometimes it really has snakes twining around it.

Info.Name: Giant Serpent Tree
Info.Desc: A giant tree which resembles two snakes intertwined. Flowers may bloom at the heads of the snakes.

Info.Name: Giant Light Serpent Tree
Info.Desc: A giant tree which resembles a golden cobra. It has unique giant leaves that look like they will bite.

Info.Name: Spook Wood
Info.Desc: A tree possessed by spooks. Its appearance has become spook-like, which makes it eerie.

Info.Name: Giant Spook Wood
Info.Desc: A great tree possessed by powerful spooks. It's bigger than usual Spook Woods, and is eerier.

Info.Name: Shadow Spook Wood
Info.Desc: A tree possessed by a shadow spook. It's even eerier, and emits a dangerous aura.

Info.Name: Spirit Tree Stormwood
Info.Desc: A floating giant tree that is tens of thousands of years old. Leader of the Spook Woods. Also known as a Spirit Tree (Giant Spirit Tree)

Info.Name: Spirit Tree Stormwood
Info.Desc: A floating giant tree that is tens of thousands of years old. Leader of the Spook Woods. Also known as a Spirit Tree (Giant Spirit Tree)
